[src:operations-research/dynamic-programming] This functional equation is known as the Bellman equation, which can be solved for an exact solution of the discrete approximation of the optimization equation.
[src:operations-research/dynamic-programming] In economics, the objective is generally to maximize (rather than minimize) some dynamic social welfare function.
[src:operations-research/dynamic-programming] In Ramsey's problem, this function relates amounts of consumption to levels of utility.
