[src:operations-research/dynamic-programming] The dynamic programming approach to solve this problem involves breaking it apart into a sequence of smaller decisions.
[src:operations-research/dynamic-programming] To do so, we define a sequence of *value functions* $V_{t}(k)$ , for $t=0,1,2,\ldots ,T,T+1$ which represent the value of having any amount of capital k at each time t.
